This clearly has improved on functionality but I find it hard to read. Let's take this example from swagger documentation.

```
{
  "200": {
    "description": "a pet to be returned",
    "schema": {
      "$ref": "#/definitions/Pet"
    }
  },
  "default": {
    "description": "Unexpected error",
    "schema": {
      "$ref": "#/definitions/ErrorModel"
    }
  }
}
```

The response object keys are **status codes** and the **default** key, so lookups were natural to read before, response-> status code -> schema. Now we destruct early (status_code, response) and that makes a lookup less intuitive and the status code variable is distantly far from where it's used again.

