We aren't trying to remove grpc from pubsub right now. The interface shouldn't include references to `google-cloud-pubsub` objects so that we can modify the underlying implementation to be non-grpc. If we modified the underlying interface _now_ then we would still have to remove references to `google-cloud-pubsub`. Instead we are laying the groundwork to make that implementation swap easy, and this is what I mean by removing any "explicit" dependencies (i.e. references) to `google-cloud-pubsub` objects.

@amartsinovich-dialpad I do agree that this is a different case because users of this lib don't have to create this `StreamingPullFuture` but instead just receive it and use it. So in that sense it's not the worst thing in the world to leave as-is. That being said, it would be nicer to return another future with the same interface or perhaps a simplified interface. Like you said re: `subscribe` deprecation, you're convincing me that this should actually be fine because we're going to nuke it anyway.

