Hey @zhuzilin, instead of removing the `@_cache`, you should be able to make the `group_lists` hashable using a simple trick.  First we can define these helper functions in `horovod/tensorflow/util.py`:

```
def vars_to_refs(vars):
    return tuple(v.ref() for v in vars)

def refs_to_vars(refs):
    return [r.deref() for r in refs]
```

Then we can use these functions to wrap the `_make_allreduce_grads_fn`:

```
@_cache
def _make_cached_allreduce_grads_fn(..., groups):
    groups = refs_to_vars(group_refs) if isinstance(groups, tuple) else groups
    ...

def _make_allreduce_grads_fn(...):
    groups = vars_to_refs(groups) if isinstance(groups, list) else None
    return _make_allreduce_grads_fn(..., groups)
```

