@richardliaw A few reasons:
1. Python lambdas use late-binding, so such closure captures would end up submitting `len(self._pipelines)` read tasks all with the same final `pipeline` query. We circumvent this by eagerly binding with default args.
2. Capturing `self` in the closure could add extra serialization bloat, e.g. it would send the full `self._pipelines` to every read task. In other datasources, this has led to serialization errors, object leaks, etc.

